channel.title: Interface configs
channel.description:
Hello, does anyone have a good list of interface configs that I can have? I've been trying to get them for days, as I'm trying to get the catapult to work in castle wars, through the dialogue. And to make the little x and numbers move, I need configs to do so. If anyone has a dump or something for them, that'd be appreciated.
Also, not sure if this is the right section for this. If it's not, please move it to where it should be.

item.title: Interface configs
item.dc:creator: @sorecheeny sorecheeny
item.description:
@sorecheeny wrote:

[quote=“Bl3nd, post:4, topic:550639”][quote author=sorecheeny link=topic=669550.msg4477232#msg4477232 date=1426730862]

Is this what you are looking for?
https://github.com/Odel/VidyaScape/blob/master/Community%20Configuration%20Package/Interfaces/317%20Interface%20Dump.txt

This is a pretty good resource that I’ve been using.

Noo, it’s not what I need. If I’m not mistaken they’re also called VarBits or something. I think in some interfaces, there’s a config in it that can make changes to contents inside of the interface, like the gnome glider. You open up the gnome glider (interface 802) and send config 153 with a value of 1-20, it’ll do something to the glider in the interface. I need the configs for the catapult interface in castle wars so I can make it functional.
[/quote]

Oh I know what your talking about but I don’t know the values… Sorry[/quote]

It’s all good, I don’t think anyone has the configs, from what I know from searching

Read full topic
